Section2.Para:
Each gathered radargram has been pre-processed by means of the following smooth standard filtering approaches [1], which have been applied according to the sequence in which they are listed


Dewow;



Background Removal (mean trace subtraction);



Linear Gain;



Vertical Band Pass Filter.

                  This preprocessing chain allows us to filter out low and high frequency noise to remove/mitigate field contributes due to direct antenna coupling and reflection from air-soil interface as well as to compensate the amplitude decay of the probing signal, while preserving, as much as possible, the original signal features.
